@startuml Logout_Sequence_Detailed
!theme blueprint
title Logout Process - Session Termination & Cleanup

actor User as U
participant "Frontend\n(blog.localtest.me:3000)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(api.localtest.me:3001)" as BE
database "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB

== Phase 1: Logout Initiation ==
U -> FE: 1. Click "Logout" button
note right: User initiates logout from interface

FE -> FE: 2. Prepare logout request
note right
**Frontend Logout Preparation:**
const logout = async () => {
  const response = await fetch(
    'http://api.localtest.me:3001/auth/logout',
    {
      method: 'DELETE',
      credentials: 'include',     // Include session cookie
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      }
    }
  );
}

**Request Details:**
- Method: DELETE (RESTful logout)
- Credentials: include (automatic cookie)
- No Authorization header needed
- Cookie-based authentication
end note

FE -> BE: 3. DELETE /auth/logout (with session cookie)
note right
**Request Headers:**
DELETE /auth/logout HTTP/1.1
Host: api.localtest.me:3001
Cookie: astral_session=session_123; domain=.localtest.me
Content-Type: application/json

**Cookie Transmission:**
- Browser automatically includes astral_session
- HTTP-only cookie not accessible via JS
- Secure transmission over network
end note

== Phase 2: Session Extraction & Validation ==
BE -> BE: 4. Extract session cookie

alt Session cookie exists
    BE -> DB: 5a. Delete session from database
    note right
    **Database Deletion Query:**
    DELETE FROM sessions 
    WHERE id = $1;
    
    **Delete:**
    - Session record (id, user_id, etc.)
    - Discord access_token
    - Discord refresh_token  
    - Session expiration data
    - Created timestamp
    end note
    
    alt Database deletion successful
        DB -> BE: 6a. Session deleted successfully
        note right
        **Success Response:**
        DELETE 1  -- One row affected
        end note
        
    else Database deletion failed
        DB -> BE: 6b. Database error
        note right
        **Possible Errors:**
        1. Connection timeout
        2. Session not found (already deleted)
        3. Database constraint violation
        4. Network connectivity issues
        
        **Error Handling:**
        - Log error details
        - Continue with cookie cleanup
        - Don't fail logout operation
        end note
    end
    
else No session cookie
    BE -> BE: 5b. Skip database operation
    note right
    **No Session Scenarios:**
    1. User already logged out
    2. Cookie expired naturally
    3. Cookie manually deleted
    4. Different browser/device
    
    **Action:** Proceed to cookie cleanup
    Still clear any remaining cookies
    end note
end

== Phase 3: Cookie Cleanup & Security ==
BE -> BE: 7. Clear session cookie (always)
note right
**Cookie Invalidation:**
set.cookie = {
  [appConfig.cookies.session.name]: {
    value: "",                    // Empty value
    httpOnly: true,               // Maintain security
    secure: false,                // HTTP in development
    sameSite: "lax",             // CSRF protection
    maxAge: 0,                   // Immediate expiration
    path: "/",                   // Same path as original
    domain: ".localtest.me",     // Same domain as original
  },
};
end note

BE -> FE: 8. Return success response
note right
**Logout Response:**
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Logged out successfully"
}

**HTTP Headers:**
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Set-Cookie: astral_session=; Max-Age=0; 
            Domain=.localtest.me; Path=/; HttpOnly
Content-Type: application/json
end note

== Phase 4: Frontend State Cleanup ==
FE -> FE: 9. Clear authentication state
note right
**Frontend Cleanup:**
// 1. Clear Pinia authentication store
authStore.clearUser();

// 2. Reset user context
authStore.user = null;
authStore.isAuthenticated = false;

// 3. Clear any cached preferences
localStorage.removeItem('userPreferences');

// 4. Reset UI to unauthenticated state

**State Management:**
- Remove user object from store
- Clear authentication flags
- Reset protected route access
- Update UI components
end note

FE -> U: 10. Navigate to /login page

BE -> BE: 12. Attempt session extraction
note right
**Session Extraction Result:**
const sessionId = extractSessionId(headers, cookie);
// Result: null (no session cookie)

**Authentication Check Fails:**
- No cookie present in request
- No Authorization header
- No X-Session-ID header
end note

BE -> FE: 13. Return authentication error
note right
**Expected Error Response:**
{
  "error": "No session found",
  "debug": {
    "cookieReceived": false,
    "authHeaderReceived": false,
    "sessionHeaderReceived": false
  }
}

**Status:** 401 Unauthorized
**Confirmation:** Logout successful
end note

FE -> U: 14. Show unauthenticated interface

@enduml
